                <h1 style='font-size:26px;'>Is there a way to enable SSL connection in OpenCart after the shop has been created?</h1>
		<div style='margin-bottom:20px; margin-top:10px; clear:both; color:#6e6e6e;'>Category: <a href='/support/community-support/opencart'>Opencart</a></div>
		<div style='margin-bottom:20px; margin-top:10px; clear:both; color:#6e6e6e;'></div>
		<div style='float:right; width:110px; margin:0px 0px 25px 25px;'>
			<img src='http://graph.facebook.com/jheri.cavitt/picture?type=normal' class='user_avatar' /><br />
			<a href='/support/community-support/users/jhericoco'>jhericoco</a>
			<div>25 <a href='/support/team/points' target='_blank'>Points</a></div>
			<div class='smallgrey' style='margin-top:10px;'>
				Asked:<br />
				2013-08-06 3:17 pm EST<br /><br />
				Hits: <span name='page_views' id='page_views'>6,772</span>
			</div>
			
		</div>
		<div>
			<div style='min-height:110px;'>I finished the site a couple of weeks ago and the client didn't originally have Authorize.net as an option. Now that we're enabling it, we have to have secure checkout pages. Is there a way to enable SSL connection in OpenCart after the shop has been created? Thanks for any assistance.<br />
<br />
fashionforprofit.com<br />
<br />
